title: For Sale:  1956 Sino-Soviet SKS
postcontent: For sale is a 1956 Sino-Soviet SKS (7.62X39).  It's in very nice condition.  It's a rather unusual gun.  When the Chinese began operation of the Jianshe arsenal in 1956, they used Russian parts for the first couple of months.  As a result, guns built during that time have the Russian serial number system of a letter followed by 4 numbers.  So it's basically a Russian gun assembled in the Jianshe plant (plant 26) (which is why it's called a Sino-Soviet).  When the Chinese began making their own parts, they used the Chinese serial number system of all numbers,  No one is quite sure how many of the Sino-Soviets were made, but it's not a lot.  This one is C 7XXX.  I'm asking $350 REDACTED

title: For Sale:  Leupold Vari-X III 6.5-20x40mm, Silver, One inch tube
postcontent:
This scope was babied its whole existence and sat for its whole life on a prissy / zero-recoiling Anschutz 22 lr benchrest model that I used as a 50-75 yard precision plinker.  I sold that rifle last year and this scope has been sitting around ever since.  It's in great condition,  functionally perfect, and nearly cosmetically perfect, and would otherwise almost pass for new except for a single, one inch long mounting mark/indentation on one side of the scope. Aside from that mark, and aside from the fact it's an older and now discontinued model, it could almost pass for new.
I will probably regret selling this scope 5 minutes after I actually do so, as my understanding is that this particular line of Leupolds was recently discontinued, and it's now impossible to get this configuration of magnification (6.5-20 power )   from Leupold in their top tier lines, for anything less than 700 dollars. And you cant get it in silver anymore either, only matte black.  The most comparable scope they apparently offer now in this configuration, is their VX-3i 6.5-20 x 40, with the only difference being a side focus adjustment now instead of the old school AO (adjustable objective) on the bell of this scope.  I would like to hold onto this scope just for value sake or future use, but just dont see how I'm going to use it again in the forseeable future, as my newest build is going to be a 1000 yard bench rig, and I'll be using my Nightforce 12-42 or the new Vortex Golden Eagle 15-60 power for that.  I just don't have anything else with a stainless finish barrel that  I shoot in the 100-200 yard range that aesthetically requires a silver scope, or this range of magnification.  So, I may as well stop hoarding and let it go while I'm in the selling mode.
